#!/home/peter/splay/.venv/bin/python
"""splay — still-image viewer with selection, wipe, thumbnail strip, and
optional image-processing apps loaded from ~/splay/apps/ and ~/.config/splay/apps/.

Usage:
    splay <files...>              # explicit list
    splay <dir>                   # all images in dir (recursive=no)
    splay                         # all images in cwd
    splay --app <name> <files>    # load an image-processing app

Keys (always):
    ← →         previous / next frame  (Shift = ±20, ≈1 min at 3s cadence)
    s           select current frame
    d           deselect current frame
    l           toggle list mode / selected-only mode
    a           cycle sort: name (alphanumeric) → age (mtime, newest first)
                  → added (load/discovery order, newest first)
    w           toggle wipe between two most recently shown frames
    f           toggle fullscreen (image only — no overlay; HUD via h)
    h           toggle HUD / help
    t           toggle thumbnail strip
    r           reload changed / pick up new files in source dirs
    R           toggle auto-reload (rescans once a second; default off)
    0           fit image to window
    1           pixel-for-pixel (100%)
    2           zoomed in (200%)
    3 / 4       FITS auto-stretch: darker / brighter (re-renders from raw)
    p           pixel data at mouse position (BGR + HSV)
    m           toggle hot-pixel mask (FITS only)
    M           toggle red highlight of hot pixels (FITS only)
    z / x       step backward / forward through sibling masks
                (siblings = hot-pixels-*.fits.fz next to the seed mask)
    g           open current frame in GIMP (FITS exported to PNG first)
    o           toggle DS9 .reg overlay (auto-loaded from sidecar)
    Delete      remove current frame from the list (does not touch disk)
    L-drag      pan the image when zoomed (1x / 2x)
    q           quit
    Esc         minimise window  (Ctrl-C in launching terminal also quits)

Keys (in --app mode):
    o           cycle view: input / wipe / output / mask
    , .         cycle which app parameter is active
    [ ]         decrement / increment active parameter by step
    { }         decrement / increment by 10× step
    0           toggle active parameter between current and default (A/B)
    Shift+0     toggle ALL parameters between current and defaults (A/B)
    z / Z       undo / redo a parameter change (clicks + key adjustments)
    Ctrl+R      open render-now dialog with current parameters
    Ctrl+S      save current parameters to a sidecar (plugin-defined)
                — sidecar is auto-loaded when the image is reopened
"""

